
Metadata extractor

Idea:
* extarct meta data from files (or existing nepomuk:resource)
* take this info and search the internet for more details
* python plugins (easy to write) handle the actual search.
* python plugins only create a simple dictionary (transformed into QVariantMap)
* the c++ part have neopomuk pipe classes, that transform such QVariantMap data into DMS calls

+ not working yet, but planned
* nepomuk resource based fetching
* mp3 support
* a lot more python plugins

#################################################################
# Dependencies:
* Nepomuk
** with nbib.ontology ~ see end of README
** SDO master for the nmm: changes with the poster/banner support

* poppler (for pdf parsing)
* Kross framework with working python interpreters
* For python: imdbpy, tvdb_api module both current master

OpenSuse user need to install the python Kross intepreters from source. see:
https://projects.kde.org/projects/kde/kdebindings/kross-interpreters/repository

#################################################################
# install to the system

mkdir build
cd build
cmake ../ -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=`kde4-config --prefix` -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=release
make
make install

and start via metadatafetcher <url to file or folder>
or via right click service menu in dolphin

#################################################################
# install necessary ontology
copy
nbib/nbib.trig
nbib/nbib.ontology

into
/usr/share/ontology/nie